OL,7,FDeputy Chief Constable Sam de Reya
OL,8,Fsaid last summer's disorder showed
OL,9,F"the major, real-world consequences"
OL,10,Fof police releasing such information
OL,11,Fto the public and hoped the change
OL,12,Fwould combat the spread of
OL,13,Fmisinformation.
OL,15,F"We have to make sure our processes
OL,16,Fare fit for purpose in an age of
OL,17,Fsocial media speculation and where
OL,18,Finformation can travel incredibly
OL,19,Fquickly across a wide range of
OL,20,Fchannels," she said.
